    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>Letronne in <bibl><ptr target="#pacho1827"/>, pl. <citedRange>74</citedRange> and pp. <citedRange>397-399</citedRange></bibl> (= 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#letronne1828"/>, pp. <citedRange>259-261</citedRange></bibl>), whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#CIG"/> <citedRange>5185</citedRange></bibl>;
                   <bibl><ptr target="#OGIS"/> <citedRange>124</citedRange></bibl>, and 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI1"/>, pp. 42-45, n. <citedRange>2</citedRange>, fig. 6</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.358</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>033800</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
                    <p>Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, p. <citedRange>398</citedRange> and p.<citedRange>483</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#lanciers1988"/>, pp. <citedRange>430-431</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#paci1996"/><citedRange/></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>46.2214</citedRange></bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#criscuolo2001b"/><citedRange/></bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>51.2213</citedRange></bibl>. 
                    </p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w lemma="βασιλεύς"><supplied reason="lost">Β</supplied>ασιλέα</w> <persName type="ruler" key="Ptolemy VIII"><name nymRef="#Πτολεμαῖος"><unclear>Π</unclear>τολεμαῖον</name></persName>, τὸν <w lemma="βασιλεύς"><unclear>βασ</unclear>ιλ<unclear>έ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ως</supplied></w>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="ruler" key="Ptolemy V"><name nymRef="#Πτολεμαῖος">Πτολεμαίου</name></persName> καὶ <w lemma="βασίλισσα"><supplied reason="lost">βα</supplied>σιλίσσ<supplied reason="lost">η</supplied>ς</w>
                        <persName type="ruler" key="Cleopatra I"><name nymRef="#Κλεοπάτρα">Κλε<unclear>ο</unclear><lb n="3" break="no"/>πάτρας</name></persName>, <persName type="ruler" sameAs="#PtolemyVIII"><w lemma="ἀδελφός">ἀδελφόν</w>, <rs type="epithet" key="Theos Philometor"><w lemma="θεός">θεὸν</w> <w lemma="φιλομήτωρ"><supplied reason="lost">Φ</supplied>ιλομήτορα</w></rs></persName>,
                    <lb n="4"/><space quantity="7" unit="character"/> ἡ <w lemma="πόλις">π<supplied reason="lost">ό</supplied><unclear>λ</unclear>ις</w> <supplied reason="lost"><space quantity="7" unit="character"/></supplied>.

	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">La statue</supplied> du roi Ptolémée, fils du roi Ptolémée et de la reine Cléopatre, le frère, Dieu Philomètôr, <supplied reason="subaudible">a été érigée par</supplied> la cité.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">The statue of</supplied> king Ptolemy, son of king Ptolemy and of queen Cleopatra, the brother, God Philometor, <supplied reason="subaudible">has been dedicated by</supplied> the city.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">La statua del</supplied> re Tolemeo, figlio del re Tolemeo e della regina Cleopatra, il fratello, Dio Filometore, <supplied reason="subaudible">è stata eretta dalla</supplied> città.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
                <p>(تمثال) الملك بتوليميوس (بطليموس)، ابن الملك بتوليميوس والملكة كليوباترا، شقيق المُؤله فيلوميتور، (كُرِس من قبل) المدينة.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                
                <p>At Ptolemais there are three similar bases for members of the Lagid family (<ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr033700</ref>, <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr033800</ref> and 
                    <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr084300</ref>), which were re-used in the same Roman monument that seems to lay upon the foundations of a Hellenistic monumental base to which 
                    they probably all belonged, perhaps along with a fourth one, now lost. The Roman monument is part of the so-called Square of the Cisterns, which may have been formerly either 
                    the gymnasium (<bibl><ptr target="#stucchi1975"/>, p. <citedRange>128, footnote 3</citedRange></bibl>) or the agora 
                    (<bibl><ptr target="#laronde1987"/>, p. <citedRange>398</citedRange></bibl>).
                    </p>
                <p>This base has long been thought to mention king Ptolemy VI Philometor; after the publication of <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr084300</ref>, it appears (<bibl><ptr target="#criscuolo2001b"/></bibl>) that the latter was dedicated to him,
	          while the present one honoured his younger brother, associated as king with him and their sister Cleopatra, whence the date.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
